	Fix crasher. uri is a string, not a MateVFSUri.

2004-11-23  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	Merged from mate-2-8:

	* file-chooser/gtkfilesystemmatevfs.c (load_dir): Use a different
	number of items per notification depending on whether the folder
	system is local or not.

2004-11-19  Christian Rose  <menthos@menthos.com>

	* configure.in: Added "rw" to ALL_LINGUAS.

2004-11-15  Dwayne Bailey  <dwayne@translate.org.za>

	* configure.in: Added "nso" to ALL_LINGUAS.

2004-11-13  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@mate.org>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.h:
	Deprecate, used by MateIconList which is also deprecated.
	
2004-11-13  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@mate.org>

	* libmate/mate-scores.h:
	Deprecate. This is too specialized, and eventually a replacement
	will find its way into mate-games.

	* libmateui/mate-about.h:
	Deprecate, use GtkAboutDialog.
	
	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.h:
	Deprecate, use GtkFileChooserButton.
	
	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.h:
	Deprecate, use GtkIconView.
	
	* libmateui/mate-pixmap-entry.h:
	Deprecate, broken widget and no-one uses it.
	
	* libmateui/mate-window-icon.h:
	Deprecate, use gtk_window_set_icon_name.

2004-11-08  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@mate.org>

	* configure.in: Update to 2.9.1

2004-09-22  J.H.M. Dassen (Ray) <jdassen@debian.org>

	http://bugzilla.mate.org/show_bug.cgi?id=153151
	* libmateui/mate-entry.h: Removed prototype for
	mate_entry_construct, as that function was removed in
	libmateui/mate-entry.c 1.68 (2001-09-04).
	* libmateui/mate-href.h: Removed prototype for mate_href_construct
	as that function was removed in libmateui/mate-href.c 1.31.2.1
	(2001-08-30).

2004-09-17  Matthias Clasen  <mclasen@redhat.com>

	* file-chooser/gtkfilesystemmatevfs.c (gtk_file_system_mate_vfs_parse): 
	Don't switch the folder until we have seen the full hostname.
	Otherwise, the auth dialog will come up for every single character
	of the hostname being typed in. (#151296, Rodney Dawes)

2004-09-13  J.H.M. Dassen (Ray) <jdassen@debian.org>

	* configure.in: Bumped the mate-vfs version requirement to 2.7.1 as
	that is the first release to have MATE_VFS_MODULE_CALLBACK_QUESTION
	which is used in libmateui/mate-authentication-manager.c's
	mate_authentication_manager_init().

==================== 2.8.0 ====================

2004-09-13  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@mate.org>

	* configure.in: Release 2.8.0
	
	* NEWS: Update

2004-09-13  Jesus Bravo Alvarez  <suso@trasno.net>

	* configure.in: Added gl (Galician) to ALL_LINGUAS.

2004-09-03  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* file-chooser/gtkfilesystemmatevfs.c: Include
	the right header so i18n works properly. Patch
	from Christian Persch <chpe at mate org>. Closes
	bug #144529.

2004-08-30  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	Merged from the mate-2-6 branch:

	Fix #145200:

	* file-chooser/gtkfilesystemmatevfs.c (struct
	_GtkFileSystemMateVFS): Added fields to store the signal
	connection IDs for the volume monitor.
	(gtk_file_system_mate_vfs_init): Store the signal connection IDs.
	Do not create an extra reference to the volume monitor.
	(gtk_file_system_mate_vfs_finalize): Disconnect from the volume
	monitor's signals.  For now, don't unref the monitor.  See
	http://bugzilla.mate.org/show_bug.cgi?id=151463 for reference.

=================== 2.7.92 ====================

