2002-11-08  Malcolm Tredinnick <malcolm@commsecure.com.au>

	A small pile of fixes to make the API docs build without
	warnings and to include all of the new thumbnail and theme
	stuff.

	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-icon-lookup.sgml,
	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-icon-theme.sgml,
	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-theme-parse.sgml,
	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-thumbnail.sgml:
	New files.

	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-typebuiltins.sgml:
	Add some type functions that come with the new functionality.

	* doc/reference/libmateui-docs.sgml,
	* doc/reference/libmateui-sections.txt:
	Update to include the new icon, theme and thumbnail files.

	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-app-helper.sgml:
	Fix the descriptions of L_() and D_().

	* doc/reference/tmpl/mate-icon-list.sgml:
	Remove a private structure from public view.

	* doc/reference/.cvsignore:
	Ignore some new files generated by gtk-doc.

	* libmateui/mate-popup-menu.c:
	Add missing documentation.

	* libmateui/mate-about.c,
	* libmateui/mate-icon-lookup.c:
	Fix some doc comments.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-lookup.h,
	* libmateui/mate-thumbnail.h:
	Remove trailing comma from last item in an enum. It is not
	portable and it also makes gtk-doc explode.

	* libmateui/mate-theme-parser.h:
	Move some comments to before a typedef definition to avoid a
	gtk-doc error. Will document this typedef properly later.

