2002-05-21  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	Accessibility support for libmateui, by several people at Ximian.

	* libmateui/libmateui-access.[ch]: New files with utility
	functions for accessibility.

	* libmateui/Makefile.am (libmateui_2_la_SOURCES): Added
	libmateui-access.[ch].

	* libmateui/mate-color-picker.c
	(mate_color_picker_instance_init): Added ATK name/description.

	* libmateui/mate-dateedit.c (create_children): Added ATK
	name/description/relations.

	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.c (mate_file_entry_init): Added ATK
	name/description/relation.

	* libmateui/mate-href.c (mate_href_instance_init): Added ATK
	name/description.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c (ientry_browse): Added ATK
	name/description.
	(mate_icon_entry_instance_init): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c: Implemented accessibility
	interfaces for the icon list widget.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-sel.c (mate_icon_selection_show_icons):
	Added ATK relation.

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap-entry.c (refresh_preview): Added ATK
	name/description.

Mon May 20 17:07:42 2002  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* configure.in: add cs to languages

2002-05-20  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@gnu.org>

	* configure.in: Release 1.117.1

2002-05-17  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@gnu.org>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.c: (mate_icon_text_item_draw):
	Draw focus correctly.
	
	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c: 
	Select the first item on focus-in, also make cursor handling a bit
	more sane. Fixes #81142, reported by Glynn Foster.
	
2002-05-17  Mark McLoughlin  <mark@skynet.ie>

	* libmateui/mate-ui-init.c: (libmateui_rc_parse): since
	this is called after gtk_rc_init, we need to parse the
	rc files instead of adding them to the list of files
	gtk_rc_init parses. Also removed FIXME, that I think this
	fixes.

Wed May 15 20:30:14 2002  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.c: remove dnd dest from the gtk entry and
	  setup dest on the whole file entry.  Also parse the uri list
	  differently, we can't use _is_local since it's not what I thought
	  it meant when I originally wrote this code.  So that for example
	  drops from applications:// won't work since we can so far only
	  handle files.  Also this will remove the drag_data_received from
	  being called twice because we set dest twice, etc...

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap-entry.c: since the drag dest is now bound
	  on the  whole file entry and we derive from it remove it from here

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c: parse the uri list in the same way
	  we do for file entry now, so that we work correctly.  We really
	  need at least a little bit of vfs support so that we could snarf
	  icons out of desktop files from the vfolders.

2002-05-15  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.c (update_pango_layout): Use
	PANGO_WRAP_WORD most of the time, until we get a word that is
	wider than the layout width.  In this case, switch to
	PANGO_WRAP_CHAR.  Fixes #78508 in a semi-ugly way, but currently
	PangoLayout provides no other way to do this.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c (gil_get_items_per_line): Do a
	slightly better computation of how many icons fit in a row, by
	remembering that there are DEFAULT_COL_SPACING pixels between the
	icons and each of the left/right edges of the window.

2002-05-14  Michael Meeks  <michael@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c: 
	(create_and_popup_toolbar_menu): update string, argh,
	tolerate odd mateconf key values.
	(toolbar_styles): correctly terminate the mateconf enum.
	(per_app_toolbar_style_changed_notify),
	(create_and_popup_toolbar_menu),
	(toolbar_style_changed_notify),
	(mate_app_setup_toolbar): repair all cut and paste in
	here so we don't SEGV on bogus mateconf key values, isn't
	mateconf enum handling great :-)

