	* libmateui.h: include mate-window-icon.h, poor
	forgotten thing.

2002-02-05  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-about.c (mate_about_instance_init): Nullify
	the initial fields.

2002-02-05  Anders Carlsson  <andersca@gnu.org>

	* configure.in: Release 1.110.1

2002-02-01  Dave Camp  <dave@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.c: (realize_cursor_gc),
	(mate_icon_text_item_realize), (mate_icon_text_item_unrealize),
	(iti_draw_cursor) : New functions to handle creating and drawing a
	cursor with the right GC.
	(iti_start_editing): Call realize_cursor_gc if the canvas is
	realized.
	(mate_icon_text_item_draw): Call iti_draw_cursor.
	(mate_icon_text_item_destroy): New function.
	(mate_icon_text_item_class_init): Initialize destroy, realize,
	and unrealize.

2002-02-01  Dave Camp  <dave@ximian.com>

	* configure.in: Bump the version number to 1.110.1.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.c: Added editing support based on the
	CajaIconTextItem object in caja.
	(draw_pixbuf_aa), (mate_icon_text_item_render),
	(iti_entry_activate), (iti_handle_arrow_key_event),
	(get_layout_index), (iti_selection_motion),
	(iti_entry_text_changed_by_clipboard),
	(iti_start_selecting), (iti_stop_selecting),
	(iti_ensure_focus), (send_focus_event),
	(mate_icon_text_item_get_editable): New functions.
	(update_pango_layout): If editing, use the GtkEntry's text instead
	of the item's text.
	(mate_icon_text_item_event), (iti_start_editing),
	(iti_stop_editing), (iti_edition_accept): Implemented.
	(mate_icon_text_item_draw): Draw the selection if text is selected,
	and draw text with the text_gc instead of fg_gc.
	(mate_icon_text_item_class_init): Initialize the render member.
	(mate_icon_text_item_configure):  Stop editing here.
	(mate_icon_text_item_get_text): Return the text in the entry if
	the item is editing.
	(mate_icon_text_item_start_editing): Call iti_ensure_focus instead
	of mate_canvas_item_grab_focus.
	(recompute_bounding_box): Use mate_canvas_item_i2w and
	mate_canvase_w3c_d to simplify the operation, and only ask for
	a bounding box big enough to display the text size.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.h: Added a create_entry virtual
	function and removed one of the padding items, and added
	mate_icon_text_item_get_editable().

	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c: (selection_one_icon_event),
	(selection_many_icon_event): Save the editing icon and
	don't try to process events meant for the editing widget.

2002-01-31  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c (real_move_cursor): Fixed
	off-by-one error; you could not focus the last icon in the list by
	pressing the Right arrow key.  Removed some ifdefed code.

