2002-01-15  Jody Goldberg <jody@mate.org>

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c (create_toolbar_item) : toggle items should use
	  "clicked" in gtk-1.3.

2002-01-14  jacob berkman  <jacob@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-druid-page-edge.c (struct _MateDruidPageEdgePrivate):
	remove canvas items and replace with widgets
	(mate_druid_page_edge_instance_init): dupicate layout of
	MateDruidPageStandard - don't use the canvas
	(mate_druid_page_edge_construct): just call various setting
	functions
	(mate_druid_page_edge_configure_canvas):
	(mate_druid_page_edge_setup): remove
	(mate_druid_page_edge_set_color): set the color like in
	MateDruidPageStandard - use the theme
	(mate_druid_page_edge_set_*): rewrite all color things to use the
	widgets
	(mate_druid_page_edge_style_set):
	(mate_druid_page_edge_realize): update the color for themes

	* libmateui/mate-druid-page-standard.c
	(mate_druid_page_standard_instance_init): redo with a different
	layout.  use a GtkTable rather than a GtkLayout - makes things
	much simpler, not lockup when shown, and fix RTL layout
	(mate_druid_page_standard_get_property): fix memory leaks with
	boxed properties
	(mate_druid_page_standard_set_property): remove redundant
	notifies
	(mate_druid_page_standard_set_*): simplify the color setting code
	(mate_druid_page_standard_set_color): simplify and update for new
	layout

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c (mate_druid_instance_init): pack the button in a
	bbox rather than placing them manually (fixes RTL issues)
	(mate_druid_destroy): destroy the bbox rather than individual
	buttons
	(mate_druid_size_request): #if 0 out the old layout, and size
	request the bbox
	(mate_druid_size_allocate): same
	(mate_druid_map): map the bbox rather than individual buttons
	(mate_druid_add): same
	(mate_druid_forall):
	(mate_druid_expose): same sort of thing
	(mate_druid_set_show_help): fix a typo such that this actually
	works correctly

