2001-12-27  jacob berkman  <jacob@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/mate-font-picker.c
	(mate_font_picker_fi_set_use_font_in_label): remove workaround as
	it has been fixed in gtk
	(mate_font_picker_fi_set_use_font_in_label): work around for gtk
	bug #67598

	* libmateui/mate-font-picker.c (mate_font_picker_set_preview_text): don't
	free/dup the text if it is the same (pointer) as our current text
	(mate_font_picker_set_font_name): ditto

	* libmateui/mate-dateedit.c (fill_time_popup): set the menu on the
	optionmenu after populating it to workaround bug #66969
	(day_selected): gtk_calendar_get_date() already returns month in
	the 0-11 range
	(select_clicked): gtk_calendar_select_month() expects month to be
	in the 0-11 range, while g_date_get_month() is 1-12.

	* libmateui/libmateuiP.h: remove _MateDialogPrivate struct.

	* libmateui/mate-dialog.h (struct _MateDialog): revert the privatization,
	as we are deprecated anyway
	* libmateui/mate-dialog.c: fix to work without ->_priv

Wed Dec 26 17:56:25 2001  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-scroes.c, mate-dateedit.c: the output of strftime is
	  not in utf8 so convert it

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap-entry.c: a bit of cleanup and remove race where
	  you could get two preview frames if you pressed the browse
	  button twice

	* libmateui/mate-scores.c: when setting font use pango, we can't use
	  gdk_fontset_load as that's deprecated, and this is non-deprecated
	  api.

	* libmateui/Makefile.am, mate-about.c, mate-app-helper.c, mate-app-util.c,
	  mate-color-picker.c, mate-dateedit.c, mate-dialog.c,
	  mate-druid-page-edge.c, mate-druid-page-standard.c,
