2001-06-04  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector-widget.[ch]: New files.

	* libmateui/mate-selector-client.[ch]: Derive from MateComponentObject, not MateComponentWidget.
	(mate_selector_client_new_from_objref): Take a MateComponent_Unknown, not a MATE_Selector.
        (mate_selector_client_construct_from_objref): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-entry.[ch]: Derive from MateSelectorWidget, not MateSelectorClient.
	(mate_entry_new_from_selector, mate_entry_construct): Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-image-entry.[ch]: Derive from MateSelectorWidget, not MateSelectorClient.
	(mate_image_entry_new_from_selector): Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-image-selector.[ch]: Derive from MateSelectorWidget, not MateSelectorClient.
	(mate_image_selector_new_from_selector, mate_image_selector_construct): Removed.

2001-06-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector-dialog-client.c
	(mate_selector_dialog_client_new): Added `MateSelector *selector' argument.

2001-06-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector-component.c (PROP_CONFIG_MONIKER, ensure_properties_handler):
	Removed; this is now done by MateSelector.

2001-06-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-entry.c: Use the new MateEntryComponent.
	(PROP_IS_FILE_ENTRY): New property; this widget can now be used both
	as normal and as file entry.

	* libmateui/mate-entry.[ch] (mate_file_entry_new): New function.

	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.[ch]: Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-selector-component.c
	(PROP_CONFIG_MONIKER): New property. This is a moniker to a MateComponent_PropertyBag
	with the default configuration (look&feel) for the selector.
	(ensure_properties_handler): Set defaults from the property bag.

2001-06-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-item.[ch]: Derive from MateCanvasText.

2001-06-02  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector-client.h (MateSelectorClientClass):
	Added "activate_entry" signal.

2001-06-01  Peter Williams  <peterw@ximian.com>

	* libmateui/pixmaps/Makefile.am (mate-stock-pixbufs.h): Add
	a $(srcdir) into the sed so we compile when builddir !=
	srcdir.

