	* configure.in: Set package name to `libmateui-2'.

2001-03-21  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	The canvas is now in its own libmatecanvas-2 top-level module.

	* libmateui/mate-canvas*.[ch]: Removed, moved to the new libmatecanvas-2
	module.

2001-03-20  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/libmateui.h (MATEUI_INIT): Don't #define this here.

	* libmateui/mate-init.c (MATEUI_INIT): Moved #define here and don't
	#include "libmateui.h".

2001-03-14  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/libmateui.h: #include "libmateui/mate-icon-selector.h" instead
	of mate-icon-sel.h.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-sel.[ch]: Moved to libcompat.

2001-03-05  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* configure.in: Depend on libmatecanvas and libxml.

	* configure.in: Set package name to `libmateui-2-martin' and
	version number to 1.96.0.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c (PROP_IS_PIXMAP_ENTRY): New boolean construction
	only property. If this is true, the widget will have the look&feel of
	the old MatePixmapEntry.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c (PROP_WANT_DEFAULT_BEHAVIOUR): New boolean property.
	If it's set, then each of the MateSelector subclasses will show its
	default behaviour, ie. whether it'll have a "Browse" button etc.
	The default for this property is TRUE so that you can now do a
	g_object_new (MATE_TYPE_ICON_ENTRY, ....) and get an object which
	actually looks like a MateIconEntry.

	If you want to set any of PROP_ENTRY_WIDGET, PROP_SELECTOR_WIDGET,
	PROP_BROWSE_DIALOG, PROP_USE_DEFAULT_ENTRY_WIDGET,
	PROP_USE_DEFAULT_SELECTOR_WIDGET, PROP_USE_DEFAULT_BROWSE_DIALOG,
	PROP_WANT_BROWSE_BUTTON, PROP_WANT_CLEAR_BUTTON or
	PROP_WANT_DEFAULT_BUTTON in g_object_new(), you need to set
	PROP_WANT_DEFAULT_BEHAVIOUR to FALSE to have this take effect.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	For MateSelector and its subclasses, you can now use g_object_new()
	to create a new instance.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelectorClass): Added `do_construct' method.
	(mate_selector_construct): Removed.
	(mate_selector_do_construct): New function, only for subclasses.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c (PROP_ENTRY_WIDGET, PROP_SELECTOR_WIDGET,
	PROP_BROWSE_DIALOG, PROP_USE_DEFAULT_ENTRY_WIDGET,
	PROP_USE_DEFAULT_SELECTOR_WIDGET, PROP_USE_DEFAULT_BROWSE_DIALOG,
	PROP_WANT_BROWSE_BUTTON, PROP_WANT_CLEAR_BUTTON,
	PROP_WANT_DEFAULT_BUTTON, PROP_AUTO_SAVE_HISTORY, PROP_AUTO_SAVE_ALL):
	New construction only properties.
	(PROP_DIALOG_TITLE, PROP_HISTORY_ID): Made these construction, but not
	construction only properties.
	(mate_selector_class_init): Connect mate_selector_constructor() to
	the GObject's `constructor' method and do_construct_handler() to the
	MateSelector's `do_construct' method.

	* libmateui/mate-entry.h (mate_entry_new_flags): Removed.
	(mate_entry_construct, mate_entry_construct_full): Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.h (mate_file_selector_new): Removed `flags'
	argument.
	(mate_file_selector_new_custom, mate_file_selector_construct):
	Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.h (mate_icon_selector_new): Removed `flags'
	argument.
	(mate_icon_selector_new_custom, mate_icon_selector_construct):
	Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.h (mate_icon_entry_construct): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_construct_full): Removed.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Back to the API described below.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h
	(MateStockPixmapEntryWidget, MateStockPixmapEntryGPixmap): Removed.
	(MateStockPixmapEntryImlib): Renamed to MateStockPixmapEntryPixbuf.
	(MateStockPixmapEntryImlibScaled): Renamed
	to MateStockPixmapEntryPixbufScaled.

	(MateStockPixmapEntryAny): Removed `width' and `height' fields;
	added `ref_count' and `pixbuf'.

	(mate_stock_pixmap_register, mate_stock_pixmap_change,
	mate_stock_pixmap_checkfor, mate_stock_transparent_window,
	mate_stock_pixmap_gdk): Replaced `const char *subtype' argument
	with `GtkStateType state'.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: Put this back to the API of MATE 1.x.
	- reverted to the state of mate-libs stable.
	- removed USE_NEW_MATE_STOCK conditional; only use the
	USE_NEW_MATE_STOCK code.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.[ch]: Tagged them as `before-martin-reverted-it'.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* demos/selector_demo.c: Added example for the new pixmap selector mode
	of the MateIconEntry.

2001-02-26  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* demos/stock_demo.c: There is no mate_stock_new_with_icon_at_size()
	any more.

	* demos/stock_demo.c: Tagged as `before-martin-reverted-it'.

