	Added "preview_x" and "preview_y" properties.

2001-02-23  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.[ch]: Moved to libcompat. This has been replaced
	by MateFileSelector.

	* libmateui/mate-mateconf.c (mate_file_entry_get/set): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_get/set): Removed.
	(mate_pixmap_entry_get/set): Removed.
	(mate_entry_get/set): Removed.

2001-02-23  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.h (MateCanvas): Removed `cc' field, GdkColorContext
	no longer exists in GTK+.

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_get_color): Use gdk_rgb_find_color()
	instead of gdk_color_context_get_pixels().
	(mate_canvas_get_color_pixel): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-line.c (mate_canvas_line_get/set_property):
	Use gdk_rgb_find_color() instead of gdk_color_context_query_color().

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-polygon.c (mate_canvas_polygon_get/set_property):
	Use gdk_rgb_find_color() instead of gdk_color_context_query_color().
	(get_color_value): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-rect-ellipse.c (mate_canvas_re_get/set_property):
	Use gdk_rgb_find_color() instead of gdk_color_context_query_color().
	(get_color_value): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-text.c (mate_canvas_text_get/set_property):
	Use gdk_rgb_find_color() instead of gdk_color_context_query_color().

2001-02-23  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/Makefile.am (INCLUDES): Added $(PANGO_CFLAGS).
	(libmateui_2_la_LDFLAGS, LDADD): Added $(PANGO_LIBS).

	* libmateui/mate-init.c (gtk_pre_args_parse): Comment out setting
	of `gtk_debug_flags' which has gone from GTK+.

2001-02-15  Darin Adler  <darin@eazel.com>

	* libmateui/mate-init.c: (mate_register_options): Use N_, not
	_, for the popt table names.
	(mate_init_with_popt_table): Remove g_free that screws up the
	popt option section.

2001-02-06  Alexander Larsson  <alexl@redhat.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-text.[ch]:
	Pango port of mate-canvas-text. Death to SuckFont, use the pango
	freetype module instead.

2001-01-29  John Harper  <jsh@eazel.com>

	* libmateui/mate-client.c (client_save_yourself_callback): commented out
	the code that sets client->save_successfull (sic) to false if
	the "save_yourself" signal wasn't emitted.

	Since the KDE session manager actually cares about the
	`success' field of the SaveYourselfDone message (unlike
	mate-session, which totally ignores it), the original logic
	had the effect of making KDE unable to shutdown when any MATE
	apps that haven't connected to the "save_yourself" signal are
	running.

	Perhaps a better fix would be to set success = False only if
	"save_session" wasn't emitted _and_ there are functions
	connected to this signal. But since it makes no difference to
	mate-session I'll leave it for now..

2001-01-15  Darin Adler  <darin@eazel.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.h: Fixed comment that was "improved" back
	in June 1999 to say the coordinates are world coordinates, when they
	are actually canvas coordinates (code and Havoc's book both say so).

	* libmateui/mate-init.c: (mate_register_options):
	Mark names of sections of the popt table with _() for translation.
	(mate_init_with_popt_table): Use a _("%s options") template for
	the main option section by default. This is better than what we had
	before, translation-wise, bug not perfect. A real fix should change
	the API of mate_init_with_popt_table so that the entire
	"xxx options" string would be localized in the main program.

2001-01-05  John Harper  <jsh@eazel.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_focus_in,
	mate_canvas_focus_out): added code to set and unset the
	HAS_FOCUS flag (which all focusable widgets should do). Without
	this patch the canvas (and thus the focused canvas item) will
	not receive focus out events

2000-12-29  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* libmateui/mate-mdi.[ch] (mate_mdi_get_children, mate_mdi_get_windows):
	new public functions for retrieving the list of children/windows.
	(mate_mdi_get_*): constified return arguments where deemed
	appropriate.

