	../demos/.

2000-12-08  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selectorP.h: Move everything but the prototypes of the
	functions which are useful for subclasses into mate-selector.c.
	This mean that mate-selectorP.h is now a semi-private header file;
	you may need to include it if you want to write your own
	MateSelector subclass.

2000-12-08  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector): The argument of the
	"set_selection_mode" signal is a GtkSelectionMode, not a gint.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector): Renamed "get_filename" signal
	to "get_uri" and "set_filename" signal to "set_uri".
	(mate_selector_get_filename): Renamed to mate_selector_get_uri().
	(mate_selector_set_filename): Renamed to mate_selector_set_uri().

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector): Renamed "update_file_list" signal
	to "update_uri_list"; removed `directory_listp' argument from the
	"get_file_list" signal and renamed it to "get_uri_list".
	(mate_selector_get_file_list): Removed `directory_listp' and renamed
	to mate_selector_get_uri_list().
	(mate_selector_set_file_list): Removed `directory_listp' and renamed
	to mate_selector_set_uri_list().
	(mate_selector_update_file_list): Renamed to
	mate_selector_update_uri_list().

	* libmateui/mate-selectorP.h (MateSelectorPrivate): Removed
	`mateconf_dir_list_key', `mateconf_file_list_key', `default_dir_list',
	`default_file_list', `dir_list', `file_list' and added
	`mateconf_uri_list_key', `mateconf_default_uri_list_key',
	`default_uri_list', `uri_list'.

Wed Dec 06 22:16:29 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c, mate-mateconf.c, mate-mdi-child.c: Cleanup,
	  setup the mateconf client data for the dockitems so that we don't crash
	  on destroy.  I've realized there are severe problems in the
	  MateUIInfo code wrt the new signal stuff and some unexplained
	  crashes.  Fun.

Wed Dec 06 20:35:48 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-mdi.[ch], mate-mdi-child.[ch], mate-mdiP.h,
	  mate-mdi-generic-child.[ch]:  fix yesterday's braindamages and
	  make signals actually work on the MDI, us ehte boilerplate on these
	  and some cleanup.  The virtual pointers in the child are now not
	  defined by the generic child typedef, since the pointers in the
	  class structure should NOT include the data pointers.  Plus it is
	  a style issue that they should be explicit types rather then
	  typedefs.

