	* libmateui/mate-animator.c: check for nulls.  If no current frame draw black.

Wed Dec 06 01:55:24 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-animamtor.c, mate-canvas.c, mate-dock-band.c,
	  mate-dock-item.c, mate-dock.c, mate-druid-page.c,
	  mate-druid.c, mate-roo.c, mate-textfu.c, gtkpixmapmenuitem.c,
	  wap-textfu.c:  There is no draw signal/method anymore, it's
	  all handled by exposes now so all the draw stuff is now gone.

2000-12-05  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selectorP.h (_mate_selector_async_handle_removed): Renamed
	to _mate_selector_async_handle_destroy().
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_removed): New internal function, does
	the opposite of _mate_selector_async_handle_add().
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_completed): Don't call the callback
	function here, only mark the async handler as completed and call
	_mate_selector_async_handle_destroy() if there are no pending sub-
	operations.

2000-12-04  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	Started to make MateSelector fully asynchronous.

	* libmateui/mate-boxed.defs (MateSelectorAsyncHandle): Added.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelectorAsyncHandle): New type.
	(MateSelectorAsyncType, MateSelectorAsyncFunc): New types.
	(MateSelector): Changed the return type of the "check_filename"
	and "check_directory" signals to void; added additional
	MateSelectorAsyncHandle parameter to the "check_filename",
	"check_directory", "add_file" and "add_file_default", "add_directory"
	and "add_directory_default" signals; removed the "do_add_*" signals.
	(mate_selector_check_filename, mate_selector_check_directory,
	mate_selector_add_file, mate_selector_add_directory): Changed return
	type to void; added three new arguments for async handling.
	(mate_selector_prepend_file, mate_selector_append_file,
	mate_selector_prepend_director, mate_selector_append_directory):
	Removed.
	(mate_selector_cancel_async_operation): New global function.
	(mate_selector_async_handle_ref, mate_selector_async_handle_unref):
	New global functions.

	* libmateui/mate-selectorP.h (MateSelectorPrivate): Added `async_ops' field.
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_get, _mate_selector_async_handle_add):
	New internal functions.
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_completed): New internal function.
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_remove): Likewise.
	(_mate_selector_async_handle_set_error): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c (set_filename_handler): Comment out call to
	mate_selector_check_filename [FIXME].

	* libmateui/mate-vfs-util.c (file_read_callback): Ignore MATE_VFS_OK since
	this may be called multiple times; on MATE_VFS_ERROR_EOF, get the
	pixbuf and call load_done(MATE_VFS_OK).

Sun Dec 03 16:37:42 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-calculator.c:  Add a bunch of xcalc like shortcuts

2000-12-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/Makefile.am (INCLUDES): Added $(WARN_CFLAGS).

	* libmateui/libmateuiP.h (mate_type_init): Added external declaration.

2000-12-01  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	A bunch of changes to make if work with the latest libraries
	again; some of them contain FIXMEs so if someone is feeling boring
	sometimes ....

	* libmateui/matemarshal.list, matemarshal-main.c: New files.
	* libmateui/libmateuiP.h: New file.

	- removed all signal marshalling functions and use the new
	glib-genmarshal tool to autogen them.

	- gdk_pixbuf_new_from_file() now takes an additional GError **
	argument [FIXME: We should find a good way to deal with such
	error conditions].

	- the GObject's "set_param" signal has a changed prototype; it now
	takes a `const MateConfValue *' instead of a `MateConfValue *'.

	- mate_client_notify_add() - the prototype of the callback function
	has changed.

	- GtkEditable has changed a lot; I #ifdef'ed most of this stuff out,
	someone with a clue must have a look at this.

	* libmateui/mate-boxed.defs (GdkImlibImage): Removed.
	(MateCanvasPoints): Added copy/free functions.

	* libmateui/maketypes.awk, matetypes.c: Merged the boxed stuff from GTK+.

Sat Nov 04 22:14:02 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/merge some patches from stable, here are the entries:
	2000-10-12  Ettore Perazzoli  <ettore@helixcode.com>

		* mate-dock-item.c: New args "preferred_width" and
		  "preferred_height".
		(mate_dock_item_class_init): Set them up.
		(mate_dock_item_get_arg): Handle them.
		(check_guint_arg): New helper function.
		(get_preferred_width): New helper function.
		(get_preferred_height): New helper function.

		* mate-dock-band.c (check_guint_arg): New helper function
		  to get a guint arg only if it exists.
		(mate_dock_band_size_request): Calculate the
		  max_preferred_width by checking the "preferred_width" or
		  "preferred_height" arg through `check_guint_arg'.
		(size_allocate_small): Changed the policy a bit so that we
		  allocate the max_preferred_width if possible.

	2000-09-24  Jody Goldberg <jgoldberg@home.com>

		* mate-dock-item.c (mate_dock_item_set_floating) : New
		  function.  set the is_floating argument of the child
		  if the child supports it.
		(mate_dock_item_detach) : Use it here.
		(mate_dock_item_attach) : Use it here.
		(mate_dock_item_remove) : Use it here.

	2000-09-23  Jody Goldberg <jgoldberg@home.com>

		* mate-dock-item.c (mate_dock_item_set_orientation) : Do
		  not hard code the use of gtktoolbar. any widget that has
		  an 'orientation' argument will do.
		(mate_dock_item_add) : Ditto.

2000-10-15  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-mateconf.c: Reflect latest MateConf API changes.
	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c: Likewise.
	* libmateui/mate-selector.c: Likewise.

2000-10-15  Chema Celorio  <chema@celorio.com>

 	* mate-window.c (mate_window_toplevel_set_title): new file &
 	function. apps should use it to set the tile, so that we can
 	have a unform way of setting the window properties (only the
 	title for now)
 	* mate-window.h: new file


2000-10-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-ditem-edit.c (fill_easy_page): Connect to the "changed" signal
	of the MateSelector rather than using the no longer existant
	mate_icon_entry_gtk_entry().

2000-10-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.h (MateIconEntry): Derive from MateFileSelector.
	(mate_icon_entry_construct_full): New function.
	(mate_icon_entry_get_icon_selector): New function.
	(mate_icon_entry_get_filename): This function is now deprecated; use
	the MateSelector functions instead.
	(mate_icon_entry_set_filename): Likewise.
	(mate_icon_entry_set_pixmap_subdir): This function is now deprecated.
	(mate_icon_entry_set_browse_dialog_title): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_set_history_id): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_pick_dialog): Removed.
 	(mate_icon_entry_set_icon): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_mate_file_entry): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_mate_entry): Removed.
	(mate_icon_entry_gtk_entry): Removed.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c: Totally rewrote this file from scratch.
	(ientry_directory_filter_func): This checks whether it's a valid
	image file [NOTE: when this is invoked from "add_file" signal handler,
	we already have the MateVFSFileInfo so this won't block; that's why
	it's better to set a filter on the MateFileSelector instead of
	overriding the "check_filename" handle.]
	(mate_icon_entry_construct_full): Create a MateVFSDirectoryFilter
	which uses the ientry_directory_filter_func() and call
	mate_file_selector_add_filter() on it.

2000-10-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-entry.h (MateEntry): Derive this from MateSelector and
	exclude all deprecated functions is MATE_EXCLUDE_DEPRECATED is
	defined.
	(mate_entry_gtk_entry): This function is now deprecated.
	(mate_entry_set_history_id): Likewise.
	(mate_entry_get_history_id): Likewise.
	(mate_entry_prepend_history): Deprecated; use the corresponding
	MateSelector function instead.
	(mate_entry_append_history): Likewise.
	(mate_entry_load_history): Likewise.
	(mate_entry_clear_history): Likewise.
	(mate_entry_save_history): Likewise.

	* libmateui/mate-entry.c (mate_entry_new_flags): New function.
	(mate_entry_construct_full): New function.

2000-09-30  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Switch to inline pixbufs.
	(default_entries_data): Removed "width" and "height".
	(stock_pixmaps): Use gdk_pixbuf_new_from_inline() with the
	inline pixbufs from pixmaps/mate-stock-pixbufs.h.

	* libmateui/pixmaps/copyright.txt: New file. This will be inserted at
	the head of the generated mate-stock-pixbufs.h.
	* libmateui/pixmaps/Makefile.am: Create mate-stock-pixbufs.h from the
	PNG images using GTK+ 2.0's make-inline-pixbuf script.

2000-09-28  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-font-selector.[ch]: Moved to libcompat.

Thu Sep 28 03:35:44 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-client.c, mate-init.c, mate_segv.c: use g_getenv
	  instead of getenv.

2000-09-25  Iain Holmes  <iain@helixcode.com>

	* libmateui/mate-propertybox.c (dialog_clicked_cb): Check all the pages for a
	change, as opposed to just the current one.
	Use the MATE_CLASS_BOILERPLATE macro for the type creation.

2000-09-24  Iain Holmes  <iain@helixcode.com>

	* libmateui/mate-recently-used.c: fix glaring compile errors/warnings :)

	* libmateui/test-recently-used.c (item_changed): Change mate_recent_document_get
	to mate_recent_document_peek.
	(add_to_menu): Same.

Sun Sep 24 04:24:34 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-pixmap.c: fix glaring compile errors/warnings

	* libmateui/mate-recently-used.c: Use GParam.  Separate the construction
	  into neccessary and lazy part.  The lazy part is the actual
	  loading of data.  This way we can do the parameter setting
	  in a minorly saner way, thus fixing problems with
	  improperly made objects, AND the ability to change app_specific
	  later (or twice) without leaks (though that's not really useful).

2000-09-24  Iain Holmes  <iain@helixcode.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-pixbuf.c: Add an ANCHOR argument, like MateCanvasImage
	has.

Sat Sep 23 17:34:17 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-calculator.c: use the mate_i18n_push/pop_c_numeric_locale

	* libmateui/mate-font-picker.c, mate-popup-help.c: include mate-i18nP.h
	  and not mate-i18n.h

Mon Sep 18 20:16:45 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-recently-used.[ch]: use boilerplates, minor cleanup,
	  some precondition checks.  Add the maximum number of documents,
	  implemented simplistically, when adding check if there is more
	  then the <key-prefix>/MaximumSize (or 30 by default), and remove
	  the oldest entries until there is this.  This really doesn't
	  need to be perfect, a simple solution is better here I think.
	  Also rename mate_recent_document_get to mate_recent_document_peek

Mon Sep 18 19:02:34 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-dateedit.c: use the boilerplate macros and switch to GParam

2000-09-16  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-mateconf.c: Very quick hack just to make it compile.

2000-09-16  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector):
	- renamed the "do_add" signal to "do_add_file".
	- added "do_add_file_default", "do_add_directory" and
	"do_add_directory_default" signals.
	- added "get_file_list" signal.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c:
	(add_file_handler): Renamed to `do_add_file_handler' and use
	the "do_add_file" signal instead of the "add_file" one.
	(add_file_default_handler): Likewise.
	(add_directory_handler): Likewise.
	(add_directory_default_handler): Likewise.
	(update_file_list_handler): Removed.
	(get_file_list_handler): New; implemnt "get_file_list" handler.

	* libmateui/mate-selectorP.h (MateSelectorPrivate): Removed `total_list'
	and `default_total_list' fields.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c (update_file_list_handler): Removed.
	(add_directory_async_handler): Call the parent handler of the
	"do_add_directory" signal.

2000-09-16  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c: Use the boilerplate macros.

2000-09-16  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c: Started to asyncify this file.
	(mate_file_selector_add_filter): New function; this lets you
	specify a MateVFSDirectoryFilter which is used when adding
	files etc.
	(mate_file_selector_clear_filter): New function; removes the
	filter again.
	(add_file_handler): Implement handler for the "add_file" signal
	of the MateFileSelector; call mate_vfs_async_get_file_info()
	with `add_file_async_cb' as async callback function.
	(add_file_async_cb): New static function;
	- if the URI is a directory, mate_selector_add_directory() it.
	- otherwise, apply the filter to it and, if it passes, emit the
	"do_add" signal.
	(add_directory_handler): Implement handler for the "add_directory"
	signal; call mate_vfs_async_load_directory_uri() on it with
	`add_directory_async_cb' as async callback function.
	(add_directory_async_cb): New static function; apply the filter
	to each of the files and emit the "add_file" signal for those who
	pass it [FIXME: at this point we already have the MateVFSFileInfo
	for the files, so basically we can filter here and emit "do_add"
	directly  ....?].
	(activate_entry_handler): Just call mate_selector_add_file();
	this should "do the right thing" even if it's actually a directory
	[FIXME: should we better async get the file info here and then
	distinguish between files and directories?].
	(check_filename_handler): If a filter is set, use it. Note
	that this is still a synchronous operation (because of the
	return value) and may block.
	(check_directory_handler): This is a synchronous operation
	as well and thus may block.

2000-09-14  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-vfs-util.h (MateGdkPixbufLoadHandle): Renamed to
	MateGdkPixbufAsyncHandle.
	(MateGdkPixbufLoadCallback): Added MateGdkPixbufAsyncHandle
	argument.
	(MateGdkPixbufDoneCallback): New callback typedef.
	(mate_gdk_pixbuf_new_from_uri_async): Added
	MateGdkPixbufDoneCallback callback function argument which
	is called when we're done reading the pixbuf.

Wed Sep 13 21:42:25 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.c: make it compile

Wed Sep 13 00:45:34 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.c: Switch to GParam, some reformatting, a hack
	  for getting style/priority right with the GParam (they need to
	  be set in unison).  Also used the boilerplate macros

