	* libmateui/mate-selector.c: Switch to GParam and use the boilerplate
	macros.

2000-09-12  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/selector-demo.c: Added MateIconEntry.

2000-09-12  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector): Added "get_filename" signal.
	(mate_selector_get_filename): New function.
	(mate_selector_set_filename): Allow the filename to be NULL.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c (mate_selector_class_init): Added the missing
	"changed" signal.
	(get_filename_handler): Default is to use "get_entry_text".
	(set_filename_handler): Allow the filename to be NULL.

2000-09-11  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.c (icon_selected_cb): New callback function;
	emits the "selection_changed" signal on the MateSelector.
	(mate_icon_selector_construct): Connect the `icon_selected_cb' to
	the "select_icon" and "unselect_icon" signals of the MateIconList.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector): Added "selection_changed" signal.

Sun Sep 10 19:47:07 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-href.[ch]: Switch to GParam, and bunches of reformatting
	  to more match standard mate style.

	* libmateui/mate-animator.c: use PARAM_ instead of ARG_ for the enum and
	  match up the names and remove an unused enum value.

Sun Sep 10 03:29:56 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-dateedit.c:  Make sure that input to gtkcalendar is legal
	  to avoid warnings.  Also use gtk_widget_size_request for the
	  calendar to make sure that the size is always querried.

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c:  When going to the next page find the next
	  visible page, rather then just any old next page.

2000-09-11  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.h (MateFileSelector): Derive from MateEntry.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c (MateFileSelectorPrivate): Removed the
	`combo' and `entry' fields.
	(get_entry_text_handler, set_entry_text_handler): Removed.
	(history_changed_handler): Removed.
	(entry_activated_cb): Moved all its functionality into the
	`activate_entry_handler' and then removed this function.
	(mate_file_selector_construct): Don't create the entry widget here
	but pass MATE_SELECTOR_DEFAULT_ENTRY_WIDGET down to the parent class.

2000-09-16  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MateSelector):
	- Added `position' argument to the "add", "add_default",
	"add_directory" and "add_directory_default" signals; this is
	0 for the start of the list, -1 for the end of it or any position
	in the middle.
	- Added "do_load" and "stop_loading" signals which are supposed
	to invoke asynchronous operations.
	(mate_selector_add_file, mate_selector_add_directory): New
	functions which allow you to insert a file or directory at an
	arbitrary position.
	(mate_selector_prepend_file,mate_selector_append_file): Call
	mate_selector_add_file() with apropriate arguments.
	(mate_selector_prepend_directory,mate_selector_append_directory):
	Call mate_selector_add_directory() with apropriate arguments.
	(mate_selector_add_file): Just emit the ADD_FILE/
	ADD_FILE_DEFAULT signal here.
	(mate_selector_add_directory): Just emit the ADD_DIRECTORY/
	ADD_DIRECTORY_DEFAULT signal here.

Fri Sep 15 18:49:34 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-animator.c, mate-helpsys.c, mate-selector.c: don't set
	  parent_class again, it's set in get_type in the boilerplates

	* libmateui/mate-ditem-edit.c: use boilerplates, remove MatePanelApplet type
	  from the default set of types.  1) it's not supported natively
	  by mate-libs, and 2) it may go away in 2.0 panel, depending
	  on how these things will be handled

Thu Sep 14 19:44:26 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-app.c: use GParam

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.c: use g_object_set/new since we now use GParam here

Thu Sep 14 18:45:54 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-file-entry.c, mate-icon-entry.c, mate-textfu.c: use
	  g_path_get_dirname instead of g_dirname

2000-09-06  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c: Removed all references to actual files and
	directories; both the file and directory lists may contain arbitrary
	text entries which don't need to be actual file or directory names.
	This is very important to allow us to subclass MateSelector for things
	which aren't files or directories; for instance a MateNumberSelector.
	(check_filename_handler, check_directory_handler): Always return TRUE.
	(set_filename_handler): Call mate_selector_check_filename() rather than
	actually checking whether it's a regular file.
	(add_file_handler, add_file_default_handler): Likewise.
	(_add_directory_handler): Removed; such things belong into
	mate-file-selector.c.
	(add_directory_handler, add_directory_default_handler): Call
	mate_selector_check_directory() and add it to the directory list on
	success; don't attempt to actually readdir() the directory.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c: This now contains the mate-vfs code to
	deal with files and directories.
	(add_directory_handler, add_directory_default_handler): Added; call
	_add_directory_handler() with appropriate `defaultp' argument.
	(_add_directory_handler): Added.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.c (append_an_icon): Use
	mate_gdk_pixbuf_new_from_uri() instead of gdk_pixbuf_new_from_file().

2000-09-06  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-vfs-util.[ch]: New files.
	These three functions are shamelessy stolen from Caja; they
	use mate-vfs to load the pixbuf so the URI doesn't need to be
	a local file.
	(mate_gdk_pixbuf_new_from_uri): New function.
	(mate_gdk_pixbuf_new_from_uri_async): New function.
	(mate_gdk_pixbuf_new_from_uri_cancel): New function.

2000-09-05  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/Makefile.am (mate_headers): Removed duplicate mate-textfu.h.

2000-09-05  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-about.c (mate_about_get_type): Removed since we now use
	the boilerplate macros.

Sat Sep 02 02:31:03 2000  Iain Holmes <terrorist@gegl.org>

	* libmateui/mate-about.c (mate_about_init): Allocate the _priv structure.
	Neatened all the functions up. Fix memory leaks. Removed needs
	for AboutInfo structure.

	* libmateui/mate-animator.c: Added GParams.

	* libmateui/gtk-clock.c (gtk_clock_new): Calls gtk_clock_construct.

	* libmateui/stock-demo.c: Help menu not right justified.

	* libmateui/mate-app.c (mate_app_set_help_view_orientation): Something wrong
	with the callback, so use the dock-items orientation value instead.

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.c: Use wap-textfu instead of textfu.
	(help_view_select_help_cb): Removed grab, set cursor to WHATISIT,
	removed sanity check. Fixed a leak too.

	* libmateui/wap-textfu.[ch]: Replacements for mate-textfu. Need renamed once
	they work to mate-textfu.[ch].

