	* libmateui/mate-animator.c: Add REVERT and RETAIN modes of animation.

2000-08-07  Karl Eichwalder  <ke@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-ditem-edit.c (fill_dnd_page): Beautify string.

2000-08-06  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	Added a default directory and file list to the MateSelector; this
	has two benefits: first of all, you can have a "Default..." button
	and when you click on it the file and directory lists are restored
	to the original. The second thing is that we can save and later load
	the current file and directory lists (for instance, when you click
	on "Browse..." and use the browse dialog to add things).

	* libmateui/mate-selector.h (MATE_SELECTOR_AUTO_SAVE_HISTORY): New flag.
	(MATE_SELECTOR_AUTO_SAVE_ALL): New flag; if set, both the file
	and directory list are saved using MateConf.
	(MATE_SELECTOR_WANT_DEFAULT_BUTTON): New flag; if set, a "Default"
	button is created which sets file and directory list to the defaults
	when clicked.
	(MATE_SELECTOR_USER_FLAGS): #define this to be a mask of flags which
	can be set in the _new() functions (G_S_AUTO_SAVE_HISTORY etc.).
	(MateSelectorClass): Added `clear_default', `add_file_default' and
	`add_directory_default' signals.
	(mate_selector_prepend_file): Added `defaultp' argument.
	(mate_selector_append_file): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_get_file_list): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_set_file_list): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_clear): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_prepend_directory): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_append_directory): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_get_directory_list): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_set_directory_list): Likewise.
	(mate_selector_set_to_defaults): New function.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.h (mate_file_selector_new): Added `flags'
	argument.
	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.h (mate_icon_selector_new): Likewise.

2000-08-06  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c: Support history loading and saving.
	(mate_selector_get_history_id, mate_selector_set_history_id):
	Removed; it makes not much sense to change this after the widget
	has been created.

Fri Aug 04 05:28:14 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.[ch]:  Add a way to get at the GtkTooltips
	  object used in mate_widget_set_tooltip and add some precondition
	  checks.

Fri Aug 04 05:08:26 2000  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libmateui/mate-helpsys.[ch]:  In the grand tradition of most probably
	  non-compiling code, I'll make it compile when I get to my machine.
	  I added private poiner and moved all the crap in there and done
	  a tiny bit of cleanup and tried to understand what this beast
	  does.

2000-08-03  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	You can now use a customize entry widget in the MateSelector.

	* libmateui/mate-selector.c (mate_selector_construct): Added `entry_widget'
	argument and added `MATE_SELECTOR_DEFAULT_ENTRY_WIDGET' enumeration
	value to the flags.
	(MateSelectorClass): Added `get_entry_text', `set_entry_text',
	`activate_entry' and `history_changed' signals.
	(mate_selector_get/set_entry_text): New functions.
	(mate_selector_activate_entry): New function.
	(mate_selector_get/set_history_id): New functions.
	(mate_selector_get/set_history_length): New functions.
	(mate_selector_append/prepend_history): New functions.
	(mate_selector_get/set_history): New functions.
	(mate_selector_load/save_history): New functions.
	(mate_selector_clear_history): New function.

	* libmateui/mate-file-selector.c: Use a GtkCombo as default entry widget.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.c: Derive from MateFileSelector.

2000-08-02  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	* libmateui/mate-icon-list.c (mate_icon_list_insert_pixbuf): Added
	`image_filename' argument.
	(mate_icon_list_append_pixbuf): Likewise.
	(mate_icon_list_get_icon_filename): New function.
	(mate_icon_list_find_icon_from_filename): New function.

	* libmateui/mate-icon-sel.c: Use mate_icon_list_get_icon_filename()
	instead of mate_icon_list_get/set_icon_data().
	* libmateui/mate-icon-selector.c: Likewise.

2000-08-01  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	Moved all deprecated files (i.e the ones that were linked into
	libmateui-1-compat and not into libmateui) into their own
	subdirectory (../libcompat).

	Hey, new you can do a `ls' here and you won't get confused by all
	this old crap any longer .... :-)

	* libmateui/mate-dentry-edit.c, mate-dentry-edit.h, mate-dns.c,
	mate-dns.h, mate-druid-page-finish.c, mate-druid-page-finish.h,
