	  it store a ref to any ditem is loads so that information not
	  updated in the gui is not lost.  Also add a whole bunch of
	  preconditions to public methods, fix the header define, added
	  accessors for new widgets, and fixed the ordering in the
	  translations list

2000-01-16  Havoc Pennington  <hp@pobox.com>

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixmap_get_draw_vals): new function
	to get the draw vals

2000-01-15  Havoc Pennington  <hp@pobox.com>

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_stock_set_icon): set main pixbuf in
	addition to the individual states.

2000-01-15  Havoc Pennington  <hp@pobox.com>

	* libmateui/mate-mdi.c (set_active_view): fix printf format warning

	* libmateui/mate-dialog.c (mate_dialog_button_clicked): remove unused
	variable

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.h: remove the "internal functions" since we no
	longer use any of them

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_stock_pixmap_gdk): gdk_pixbuf_render_pixmap

	* libmateui/mate-init.c (libmateui_pixbuf_image_loader):
	gdk_pixbuf_render_pixmap

	* libmateui/mate-calculator.c (mate_calculator_realized): replace
	mate_pixbuf_render with gdk_pixbuf_render_pixmap

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_stock_set_icon): sync with
	mate_pixmap_set_state_pixbufs rename

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c (mate_druid_size_request): add cast to remove
	warning
	(mate_druid_paint): delete prototype, never defined

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixmap_set_state_pixbufs): rename from
	mate_pixmap_set_pixbufs_at_state for clarity

	* libmateui/mate-messagebox.c: include matelib-init isntead of
	matelib-init2

	* libmateui/mate-client.c (mate_client_pre_args_parse): const on the
	module info
	(mate_client_post_args_parse): ditto

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c: There was massive cut-and-paste fest in here;
	clean it all up.  Also, remove mate_pixbuf_render since we have
	one of these in gdk-pixbuf now.
	(mate_pixmap_size_request): implement size request so we can
	lazily calculate size information instead of updating the
	requisition all the darn time
	(set_pixbuf): don't calculate any pixbufs/masks etc. since
	it's all done lazily now
	(mate_pixmap_set_draw_vals): queue a redraw if necessary

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.h: split the data members so that generated
	images are always clearly separated from non-generated images,
	this is the only way to get predictable, consistent behavior.

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c: nuke all the crufty unused code at the bottom

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.h: s/MatePixmapDraw/MatePixmapDrawMode/g

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixmap_set_pixbuf): if width/height are
	-1, it's necessary to reset the scaled image
	(mate_pixmap_set_pixbufs_at_state): call set_pixbuf_size()
	instead of manually calculating the requisition

