	* libmateui/mate-pixmap-entry.c: Port to gdk-pixbuf
	(setup_preview): port to gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixbuf_build_insensitive): init width and
	height variables

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c (create_pixmap): fix cast on xpm data to
	match const char**

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixmap_new_from_xpm_d_at_size): const on
	the xpm_data
	(mate_pixmap_new_from_xpm_d): ditto

	* libmateui/mate-messagebox.c (mate_message_box_newv): Port to new MatePixmap
	(mate_message_box_new): Port to new MatePixmap

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (set_pixmaps): Allow pixmaps/masks to be NULL for "unset"
	(set_pixbufs): Ditto
	(set_pixbuf): Ditto
	(mate_pixmap_clear): New function to clear all pixmaps

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c (mate_druid_init): port to gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c (create_pixmap): Use
	mate_stock_new_with_icon() instead of mate_stock_pixmap_widget()

	* libmateui/mate-icon-entry.c (entry_changed): port to gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixbuf_scale): If new w/h are the same as
	old w/h just use memcpy() instead of scaling.
	(mate_pixmap_set_pixbuf_at_size): New function
	(mate_pixmap_set_pixbuf): New function
	(set_pixbuf): New function, used by set_pixbufs and above two
	functions. Also implements automatic mask generation.

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.h: add a little comment about not using MatePixmap
	as an image loader.

	* libmateui/mate-druid.h: include mate-defs.h

	* libmateui/mate-druid-page.h: include mate-defs.h

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c: Don't include mate.h

	* libmateui/libmateui.h: Comment out animator, canvas image, canvas load
	headers for now.

	* libmateui/Makefile.am: Comment out mate-canvas-load.c
	(INCLUDES): Remove GDK_IMLIB_CFLAGS

	* libmateui/mate-canvas-load.h: Delete header contents; they aren't needed
	with gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/Makefile.am: Comment out mate-canvas-image.c for now

	* libmateui/mate-calculator.c (mate_calculator_realized): port to
	gdk-pixbuf; was using MatePixmap just to load an image (please
	people, could we be ANY MORE BROKEN in a million years? MateAbout
	and MateAnimator were doing the same thing)
	(put_led_font): Port to gdk-pixbuf, and don't draw with the image
	if we failed to load it.

	Note that MateCalculator is still broken because the font pixmap
	is leaked if you destroy all the outstanding MateCalculator
	widgets. Should probably use a GdkPixbuf as the representation
	instead of creating a pixmap, and render from client side. Then
	refcount the GdkPixbuf.

	* libmateui/Makefile.am: Comment out mate-animator.c for now

	* libmateui/mate-animator.c
	(mate_animator_append_frame_from_mate_pixmap): Deleted this
	function. It makes no sense, doesn't work with new MatePixmap,
	and was marked experimental.
	(free_all_frames): port to gdk-pixbuf
	(mate_animator_append_frame_from_imlib_at_size): Removed
	(mate_animator_append_frame_from_imlib): Removed
	(mate_animator_append_frames_from_imlib_at_size): Removed
	(mate_animator_append_frames_from_imlib): Removed

	* libmateui/mate-about.c (mate_about_construct): port to gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixbuf_render): Render a pixbuf to pixmap/mask

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_pixmap_button): Remove some weird pixmap
	registration stuff that no longer works and I don't understand the
	purpose of.
	(mate_pixmap_button): Unref the pixmap if it isn't placed in the
	button due to user preferences. Long-standing mem leak.
	(mate_stock_pixmap_gdk): Port to gdk-pixbuf
	(mate_stock_transparent_window): port to gdk-pixbuf

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: rename mate_stock_pixmap_checkfor() to
	mate_stock_pixmap_lookup()

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Rewrite the stock pixmap hash. We now store
	entries for all 5 states, and we do a single lookup to get all
	five states at once. Also, the MateStock widget now simply gets a
	reference to the GdkPixbuf stored in the hash. We also free memory
	associated with unscaled pixbufs, filenames, etc. once we have the
	final pixbuf cached.
	(mate_stock_new): Set MATE_PIXMAP_KEEP_PIXBUF mode since we are
	usually using a pixbuf shared with other MateStock widgets.
	(mate_stock_set_icon): Implement
	(mate_stock_pixmap_register): Don't return success/failure, that
	makes no sense (it always succeeded anyway)
	(mate_stock_pixmap_change): Ditto

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: Replace all "subtype" string arguments with
	GtkStateType enum arguments.

1999-11-04  Jonathan Blandford  <jrb@redhat.com>

	* libmateui/mate-druid.c (mate_druid_init): patch from boc to give the
	next button the focus.

1999-11-04  Havoc Pennington  <hp@pobox.com>

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Remove MateStockPixmapEntryWidget and
	MateStockPixmapEntryGPixmap; these no longer make any sense.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: MateStockPixmapEntry made opaque, all struct
	contents moved to mate-stock.c. Added new constructors and
	destructors for creating a MateStockPixmapEntry.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Removed functions I removed from the header last
	week (deprecated stuff that had been spewing warnings or not
	compiled at all).

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: MateStockPixmapEntryRGB,
	MateStockPixmapEntryRGBScaled added to replace Imlib versions

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c (mate_pixbuf_scale): Add this here; it's
	scale_down originally in mate-stock.c. We no longer handle
	the magic alpha color, and we do handle full alpha.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_stock_set_icon): Don't return success or
	failure; if the icon doesn't exist, spew warnings.
	(mate_stock_set_icon_at_size): ditto
	(mate_stock_new_with_icon): don't check return val from set_icon
	(mate_stock_set_icon): Check whether the new icon is the same as
	the old right at the start of the function.
	(scale_down): mostly moved to mate-pixmap.c as mate_pixbuf_scale()


1999-11-04  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@redhat.com>

	* libmateui/mate-app-helper.c: Patch from Eric Gillespie,
	Jr. (epg@pobox.com).  The About item should not have ellipsis.

1999-11-03  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@redhat.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_item_get_bounds): Fixed ordering of
	bounding vertices.  Now we *do* return the correct bounding box.

1999-11-03  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@redhat.com>

	* libmateui/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_init): Fixed long-standing problem
	with the canvas->pick_event not being properly initialized.  This
	caused spurious EnterNotify events to be sent to items right after
	the canvas was created and the mouse had never been inside it.

1999-11-02  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@online.no>

	* libmateui/mate-druid-page-standard.c: #include <config.h>
	* libmateui/mate-druid-page-start.c: ditto.
	* libmateui/mate-druid-page-finish.c: ditto.
	* libmateui/mate-druid-page.c: ditto.
	* libmateui/mate-druid.c: ditto.
	* libmateui/mate-stock.c (mate_pixmap_button): Marked label creation
	with _() to make buttons translatable.

1999-10-26  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka.mocnik@kiss.uni-lj.si>

	* libmateui/mate-mdi.c (mate_mdi_remove_view): if a registered object exists,
	destroy an empty MateApp even if it is the last one.

1999-10-25  Havoc Pennington  <hp@pobox.com>

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.c: set parent_class to NULL

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: Further enhance the mate-stock header. Remove
	all functions that spew "don't use me" when used; group things
	logically; add new _at_size() constructor and mutator for the
	MateStock widget.

	* libmateui/mate-pixmap.h, mate-pixmap.c: Rewrite. Now supports a
	different pixmap for every state, so we can migrate this
	functionality out of MateStock. Also, uses gdk-pixbuf instead of
	Imlib, and on Owen's recommendation does not use a shaped window.
	Also, now derives from GtkMisc so you can set alignment, etc.
	Compat functions not yet in place. Doesn't compile either,
	untested and depends on some nonexistent GdkPixbuf stuff.

	* libmateui/mate-stock.c: Delete all the stuff that wasn't being compiled
	due to the USE_NEW_MATE_STOCK #define

	* libmateui/mate-stock.h: Don't define USE_NEW_MATE_STOCK, unconditionally
	compile the new stuff, delete the old stuff.
	Move all MATE_STOCK_* string constant macros to mate-stock-ids.h
	Delete large comment at the top, it was outdated.
	Delete Imlib entry types (need compat for these)
	Make xpm_data in the XPM entry type const
	Delete all the regular/disabled/focus fields in MateStock widget

	* libmateui/mate-stock-ids.h: New file to unclutter mate-stock.h


